body_html: I ran the benchmark using all available cores on 10x the number of tensor elements. This gives an average speedup of 2.5x+ across all data types in comparison to numpy on my machine.

body: I ran the [benchmark using all available cores](https://paste.fedoraproject.org/paste/BrNjjyaoLdC~Vpi8DdhUNA) on 10x the number of tensor elements. This gives an average speedup of 2.5x+ across all data types in comparison to numpy on my machine.
